The paper deals with the problem of device detection and resource allocation in M2M communication networks, which involves signal processing, information theory, and networking aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of communication and information processing. The paper also involves the use of compressed sensing techniques for signal recovery, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper deals with the design and optimization of M2M communication systems, which can be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The proposed scheme also involves the use of machine learning algorithms for device ranking, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves simulations and performance evaluation, which can be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
